The documents indicate that the ARRB was negotiating with the CIA to declassify records, but the CIA was concerned about protecting sensitive Agency equities and operational details. The documents mention the protection of LITAMIL-9, Richard Gibson (CIA Asset), CIA official files, Mexico City tapes, and alias documentation. The documents do not provide specific details about C. Tracy Barnes' direct involvement in the JFK assassination, but rather his name appears in the context of protecting CIA equities during the declassification process.
